channel.title: I can't get my server online!
channel.description: ok... i port forwarded the port "43594" in my router, i ran the server then the client. i had my friend try and connect with the same client. He was running the same server and client and he entered my ip... and he still could not connect. If anyone has solutions on how to get it going plz respond! and i know i did the port forward right cause i watched the video and also did the port checker.

item.title: I can't get my server online!
item.dc:creator: @o0o o0o
item.description:
@o0o wrote:

If you portforwarded right and he’s running the same client, then the only thing that could be wrong is that he didn’t enter your IP correctly. Are you using a 508+? If he’s not using an IP changer client then he’ll need to compile after editing the client to have the same IP as yours.

Assuming you really did portforward correctly, that’s the only thing I could think of.
